==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Nativism
<hw>Na"tiv*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
disposition to favor the native inhabitants of a country, in preference
to immigrants from foreign countries.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Philos.)</fld> <def>The doctrine of innate ideas,
or that the mind possesses forms of thought independent of
sensation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nativist</ent>⟦br⟧
